  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN389-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. ātaṉuṅkaṉaik kaḷḷilāttiraiyaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN389">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>nīrnuṅkiṉ kaṇvalippak</l>
<l>kāṉavēmpiṉ kāytiraṅkak</l>
<l>kayaṅkaḷiyuṅ kōṭaiyāyiṉu</l>
<l>mēlā veṇpoṉ pōruṟu kālai</l>
<l>yemmu muḷḷumō piḷḷaiyam poruna</l>
<l>ṉeṉṟīt taṉaṉē yicaicā ṉeṭuntakai</l>
<l>yiṉṟuceṉ ṟeytum vaḻiyaṉu mallaṉ</l>
<l>celiṉē kāṇā vaḻiyaṉu mallaṉ</l>
<l>puṉṟalai maṭappiṭi yiṉaiyak kaṉṟutantu</l>
<l>kuṉṟaka nallūr maṉṟattup piṇikkuṅ</l>
<l>kalliḻi yaruvi vēṅkaṭaṅ kiḻavōṉ</l>
<l>celvuḻi yeḻāa nallēr mutiya</l>
<l>ṉāta ṉuṅkaṉ pōla nīyum</l>
<l>pacitta vokkaṟ paḻaṅkaṇ vīṭa</l>
<l>vīṟucā ṉaṉkala nalkumati peruma</l>
<l>vaitaka lalkuṉ makaḷir</l>
<l>neytalkē ḷaṉmār neṭuṅkaṭai yāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Saying (6a)</l>
<l>“when they force the watery eye of the palmyra fruit, (1)</l>
<l>when the unripe fruit of the forest neem becomes dry, (2)</l>
<l>even though there is west wind that dries up the ponds, (3)</l>
<l>at the time when there is war about the white gold that is not received, (4)</l>
<l>will he remember us, too, the youthful fighter?”,</l>
<l>he gave, a paragon worth of fame. (6)</l>
<l>He is not one on a way where he has gone [and] will reach today. (7)</l>
<l>He is not one on a way where he won’t be seen when going. (8)</l>
<l>The lord of Vēṅkaṭam with waterfalls falling from rocks, (11)</l>
<l>where, while the ruddy-headed elephant cows are desperate, they bring calves (9)</l>
<l>[and] tie them up on the village common of the good village inside the hills, (10)</l>
<l>Mutiyaṉ with a good plough that does not rise while going, (12)</l>
<l>Ātaṉunkaṉ, like him you too (13)</l>
<l>grant many vessels worth of pre-eminence, o great man, (15)</l>
<l>so that the distress of [my] famished kinfolk is destroyed. (14)</l>
<l>Women with wonderfully wide hips (16)</l>
<l>won’t hear the Neytal [tune] at the tall gate. (17)</l>
</lg>
